        -:   29:/** \class VectorBlock
        -:   30:  * \ingroup Core_Module
        -:   31:  *
        -:   32:  * \brief Expression of a fixed-size or dynamic-size sub-vector
        -:   33:  *
        -:   34:  * \tparam VectorType the type of the object in which we are taking a sub-vector
        -:   35:  * \tparam Size size of the sub-vector we are taking at compile time (optional)
        -:   36:  *
        -:   37:  * This class represents an expression of either a fixed-size or dynamic-size sub-vector.
        -:   38:  * It is the return type of DenseBase::segment(Index,Index) and DenseBase::segment<int>(Index) and
        -:   39:  * most of the time this is the only way it is used.
        -:   40:  *
        -:   41:  * However, if you want to directly manipulate sub-vector expressions,
        -:   42:  * for instance if you want to write a function returning such an expression, you
        -:   43:  * will need to use this class.
        -:   44:  *
        -:   45:  * Here is an example illustrating the dynamic case:
        -:   46:  * \include class_VectorBlock.cpp
        -:   47:  * Output: \verbinclude class_VectorBlock.out
        -:   48:  *
        -:   49:  * \note Even though this expression has dynamic size, in the case where \a VectorType
        -:   50:  * has fixed size, this expression inherits a fixed maximal size which means that evaluating
        -:   51:  * it does not cause a dynamic memory allocation.
        -:   52:  *
        -:   53:  * Here is an example illustrating the fixed-size case:
        -:   54:  * \include class_FixedVectorBlock.cpp
        -:   55:  * Output: \verbinclude class_FixedVectorBlock.out
        -:   56:  *
        -:   57:  * \sa class Block, DenseBase::segment(Index,Index,Index,Index), DenseBase::segment(Index,Index)
        -:   58:  */
        -:   59:template<typename VectorType, int Size> class VectorBlock
        -:   60:  : public Block<VectorType,
        -:   61:                     internal::traits<VectorType>::Flags & RowMajorBit ? 1 : Size,
        -:   62:                     internal::traits<VectorType>::Flags & RowMajorBit ? Size : 1>
        -:   63:{
        -:   64:    typedef Block<VectorType,
        -:   65:                     internal::traits<VectorType>::Flags & RowMajorBit ? 1 : Size,
        -:   66:                     internal::traits<VectorType>::Flags & RowMajorBit ? Size : 1> Base;
        -:   67:    enum {
        -:   68:      IsColVector = !(internal::traits<VectorType>::Flags & RowMajorBit)
        -:   69:    };
